  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1984-10-03", 
    "text": "Amends the Trade Act of 1974 to direct the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President pro tempore of the Senate to each select five members of their respective houses to be congressional advisors to the President with respect to implementing the comprehensive steel policy announced on September 18, 1984. Directs the U.S. Trade Representative to keep each congressional advisor informed on actions taken to implement and subsequently monitor such policy. Directs the President to establish industry and labor advisory committees to provide advice and counsel on the implementation of such policy."
  }, 
